President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued a memorandum delegating authority to the Secretary of State under section 614(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. This authority allows the Secretary of State to determine whether it is necessary for the security interests of the United States to provide up to $205 million from the Economic Support Fund. This fund will be used to advance food security and energy resilience, as well as counter the efforts of the People's Republic of China. The memorandum also directs the publication of this delegation of authority in the Federal Register.